! AudioSuite Transcription Configuration

These settings control the AI-powered transcription feature in the waveform editor.

!! Setup

# Obtain an API key from [[OpenAI|https://platform.openai.com/api-keys]]
# Paste it into the [[API Key|$:/plugins/NoteStreams/AudioSuite/configuration/transcriptions/api-key]] tiddler
# (Optional) Set your preferred [[language|$:/plugins/NoteStreams/AudioSuite/configuration/transcriptions/language]] for faster, more accurate results
# (Optional) Add a [[prompt|$:/plugins/NoteStreams/AudioSuite/configuration/transcriptions/prompt]] with names and terms that appear in your audio

!! Settings

|!Setting|!Tiddler|!Default|
|API Key|[[api-key|$:/plugins/NoteStreams/AudioSuite/configuration/transcriptions/api-key]]|//empty — required//|
|Model|[[model|$:/plugins/NoteStreams/AudioSuite/configuration/transcriptions/model]]|`whisper-1`|
|Language|[[language|$:/plugins/NoteStreams/AudioSuite/configuration/transcriptions/language]]|//auto-detect//|
|Endpoint|[[endpoint|$:/plugins/NoteStreams/AudioSuite/configuration/transcriptions/endpoint]]|`https://api.openai.com/v1/audio/transcriptions`|
|Prompt|[[prompt|$:/plugins/NoteStreams/AudioSuite/configuration/transcriptions/prompt]]|//empty//|
|Editor Model|[[editor-model|$:/plugins/NoteStreams/AudioSuite/configuration/transcriptions/editor-model]]|`gpt-4.1-nano`|
|Editor Prompt|[[editor-prompt|$:/plugins/NoteStreams/AudioSuite/configuration/transcriptions/editor-prompt]]|//empty//|
|Editor Endpoint|[[editor-endpoint|$:/plugins/NoteStreams/AudioSuite/configuration/transcriptions/editor-endpoint]]|`https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions`|

!! Usage

* Click the ''🎤 Transcribe'' button in the waveform editor toolbar, or press ''T'' while the waveform canvas is focused
* The selected region will be extracted, encoded as WAV (mono, 16kHz), and sent to the API
* The transcription text will be saved to the notation tiddler's `transcription` field
* A `transcribed` tag will be added to the notation tiddler

!! Notes

* ⚠️ The API key is stored in ''plaintext'' within your wiki file. Only use this feature in personal or local wikis.
* The Whisper API has a 25MB file size limit. A 5-minute mono 16kHz WAV is approximately 10MB.
* Regions longer than 10 minutes will still be sent but may take longer to process.
* You can override the endpoint to use a local Whisper server (e.g. `whisper.cpp` or `faster-whisper`) or Azure OpenAI.
